      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "Please do not stop taking your prescribed warfarin without consulting your doctor first. Suddenly stopping anticoagulants can be extremely dangerous and lead to dangerous clotting events. While some foods and supplements can affect blood thinning, they are not a safe or reliable replacement for prescription medication. You must discuss any dietary changes or supplement plans with your healthcare provider.",
